1
00:00:14,480 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,200
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:01,360
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,360
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 14]

23
00:01:39,080 --> 00:01:41,880
If you get tired or hungry,
just come over.

24
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:44,720
There'll always be a bowl of noodles
saved for you.

25
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:48,200
I know you're good to me.

26
00:01:48,680 --> 00:01:50,440
I keep it all right here.

27
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,560
I'm old now.

28
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,080
Don't want to be a burden.

29
00:02:04,680 --> 00:02:05,720
Look at you.

30
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,480
You're in your prime.

31
00:02:08,840 --> 00:02:10,080
And so pretty.

32
00:02:11,760 --> 00:02:12,640
Why waste your time

33
00:02:13,040 --> 00:02:15,520
on an old man like me?

34
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:13,160
[Xiangliang 15115]

35
00:03:14,080 --> 00:03:15,080
Chen.

36
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:18,120
Chen Sanhe!

37
00:03:21,640 --> 00:03:22,440
Cheers!

38
00:03:47,720 --> 00:03:51,640
[Xiangliang 15115]

39
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,040
Cong.

40
00:04:04,760 --> 00:04:05,640
Look on the bright side.

41
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,280
I've always thought

42
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:15,960
that kind of loneliness in the dark

43
00:04:16,760 --> 00:04:19,280
is like being locked in a black box.

44
00:04:19,960 --> 00:04:21,360
He keeps screaming for help,

45
00:04:21,360 --> 00:04:22,520
but nobody answers.

46
00:04:23,400 --> 00:04:25,680
We can never understand
that kind of pain.

47
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:29,240
So maybe death

48
00:04:29,240 --> 00:04:31,360
wasn't such a bad thing for your mentor.

49
00:04:33,560 --> 00:04:36,000
Did he say anything
before he passed away?

50
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:37,720
He was lucid at the end.

51
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:39,720
Director Huang said
it was a final rally.

52
00:04:40,080 --> 00:04:41,360
Your mentor told me a lot.

53
00:04:41,720 --> 00:04:42,920
Did he mention me?

54
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:44,720
Of course he did.

55
00:04:46,520 --> 00:04:47,120
Chen.

56
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:53,200
You're asleep?

57
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,480
I heard

58
00:04:56,480 --> 00:04:58,640
you cheated death.

59
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:03,200
The King of Hell took one look at me
and said,

60
00:05:03,640 --> 00:05:04,200
"Go back.

61
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:07,200
Bring Xiang Xiuyuan with you."

62
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:10,520
Alright.

63
00:05:10,520 --> 00:05:12,120
Looks like you're clear-headed.

64
00:05:12,840 --> 00:05:14,400
You just got better.
What are you so busy with?

65
00:05:16,160 --> 00:05:16,920
Well,

66
00:05:20,080 --> 00:05:21,360
I've been out of it for three years.

67
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:24,840
I figured while I'm lucid,

68
00:05:25,080 --> 00:05:28,320
I'd write down what I can remember

69
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,120
for Cong.

70
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:33,120
Cong didn't come?

71
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,400
Cong.

72
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,800
He's a section director now.

73
00:05:37,840 --> 00:05:39,840
He's swamped. Can't make it.

74
00:05:40,040 --> 00:05:42,320
What,
I'm not good enough company for you?

75
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:44,600
You are.

76
00:05:44,960 --> 00:05:45,520
Of course.

77
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,160
You are.

78
00:05:47,840 --> 00:05:51,080
I've got something private to tell Cong.

79
00:05:51,840 --> 00:05:53,960
You wouldn't get it.

80
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,400
What kind of wise words?

81
00:05:56,400 --> 00:05:57,120
Here.

82
00:05:57,880 --> 00:05:58,920
I'm all ears.

83
00:06:00,440 --> 00:06:02,000
Don't tell anyone else.

84
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,520
Go ahead.

85
00:06:04,960 --> 00:06:06,200
Over the past three years,

86
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:07,600
I

87
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:09,320
have been in

88
00:06:10,040 --> 00:06:10,760
and out of it.

89
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,240
Xiang.

90
00:06:14,400 --> 00:06:16,440
Be honest with me.

91
00:06:17,320 --> 00:06:20,160
Are Sa Ziyi and Group E

92
00:06:20,160 --> 00:06:22,320
back in business?

93
00:06:24,760 --> 00:06:27,080
You know Customs has rules.

94
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,960
I can't know anything about that.

95
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:34,760
But I did hear there's some video

96
00:06:34,760 --> 00:06:36,560
making the rounds online.

97
00:06:36,560 --> 00:06:37,960
Something about a doll

98
00:06:37,960 --> 00:06:38,680
or whatever.

99
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:39,720
Let me see.

100
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:40,960
Come on. Let me see.

101
00:06:41,880 --> 00:06:43,240
Let me see if I can find it.

102
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:48,080
Is this it?

103
00:06:52,680 --> 00:06:53,880
It's that doll.

104
00:06:54,000 --> 00:06:54,760
That's the one.

105
00:06:55,360 --> 00:06:56,120
That's the one!

106
00:06:59,080 --> 00:06:59,800
Three years…

107
00:07:00,400 --> 00:07:02,200
Cong still hasn't caught him?

108
00:07:03,280 --> 00:07:03,960
What,

109
00:07:04,120 --> 00:07:06,000
they can't do anything

110
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:06,800
without me?

111
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,960
I can't believe

112
00:07:09,000 --> 00:07:10,240
I thought

113
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:12,520
he had what it takes for Customs.

114
00:07:24,280 --> 00:07:24,920
Here.

115
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:38,040
[Dolls → Poisonous Perfume
Let It Go]

116
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:39,400
Don't say any more.

117
00:07:39,400 --> 00:07:40,240
You just got a little better.

118
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,200
Can't get this worked up.

119
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:41,840
Xiang.

120
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,200
Please do me a favor.

121
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,640
Go on.

122
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:52,640
[Let]

123
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,120
[Let It Go]

124
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,840
Stay calm.

125
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:00,560
I'll go get a doctor.

126
00:08:00,600 --> 00:08:01,200
Xiang.

127
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:01,720
Xiang.

128
00:08:01,720 --> 00:08:02,480
Stay calm!

129
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,200
- Don't get worked up. - Don't go.

130
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,160
I'm getting a doctor.

131
00:08:04,160 --> 00:08:05,000
Xiang.

132
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,720
Xiang, don't…

133
00:08:05,760 --> 00:08:06,320
Don't go.

134
00:08:06,320 --> 00:08:07,560
- Doctor. - Don't go.

135
00:08:07,560 --> 00:08:08,440
Doctor!

136
00:08:15,840 --> 00:08:18,400
[Let It Go]

137
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:29,920
[Let It Go]

138
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:33,840
[Dolls → Poisonous Perfume
Let It Go]

139
00:08:41,320 --> 00:08:42,080
Cong,

140
00:08:43,840 --> 00:08:45,440
don't take what your mentor said

141
00:08:45,440 --> 00:08:46,920
too much to heart.

142
00:08:47,720 --> 00:08:49,560
He's ill, after all.

143
00:08:53,720 --> 00:08:55,520
If, in these three years,

144
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,920
I'd cracked Group E

145
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,240
and found who's behind it,

146
00:09:06,400 --> 00:09:08,880
my mentor wouldn't feel so helpless.

147
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,560
I don't like hearing that.

148
00:09:12,040 --> 00:09:13,320
You've done great,

149
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:14,120
you know that?

150
00:09:17,280 --> 00:09:19,520
Not finishing
what your mentor asked you to do

151
00:09:19,520 --> 00:09:20,720
is part of it.

152
00:09:22,040 --> 00:09:25,360
What really tore him apart was

153
00:09:25,360 --> 00:09:27,320
that he personally destroyed

154
00:09:27,920 --> 00:09:29,360
the faith he'd held his whole life.

155
00:09:30,000 --> 00:09:31,760
[Dolls → Poisonous Perfume
Let It Go]

156
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,360
Son, you're back.

157
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:46,640
Mrs. Guo.

158
00:09:46,640 --> 00:09:47,080
Hey.

159
00:09:48,400 --> 00:09:49,400
Have you guys eaten?

160
00:09:49,520 --> 00:09:50,360
Not yet.

161
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:53,320
How about I make you some noodles?

162
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:54,280
Not for now.

163
00:09:57,920 --> 00:09:58,960
I'm going to my room.

164
00:09:59,320 --> 00:09:59,840
Okay.

165
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:14,640
Where are you going?

166
00:10:16,360 --> 00:10:17,480
Get him some water.

167
00:10:17,480 --> 00:10:18,280
Don't bother.

168
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:21,240
His master's death hit him hard.

169
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,400
He's hurting and wants to be alone.

170
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:25,080
He carries a lot on his mind.

171
00:10:25,280 --> 00:10:26,520
He needs time

172
00:10:26,520 --> 00:10:28,520
to sort through everything on his own.

173
00:10:50,880 --> 00:10:52,640
He was the same way

174
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:53,920
when his father passed away.

175
00:10:54,440 --> 00:10:56,440
Locked himself in his room for a month.

176
00:10:56,800 --> 00:10:58,040
Wouldn't even go to school.

177
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,960
If you hadn't been there for him,

178
00:11:01,280 --> 00:11:02,560
I don't know what I would've done.

179
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:03,680
This time,

180
00:11:03,880 --> 00:11:06,000
you really need to
talk some sense into him.

181
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:06,720
Alright?

182
00:11:06,720 --> 00:11:07,560
He listens to you.

183
00:11:07,760 --> 00:11:08,520
Don't worry.

184
00:11:08,520 --> 00:11:09,640
I'll spend time with him

185
00:11:09,640 --> 00:11:10,800
whenever I can.

186
00:11:12,040 --> 00:11:14,120
Cong's not a kid anymore.

187
00:11:14,280 --> 00:11:16,200
He needs his space now.

188
00:11:16,200 --> 00:11:18,120
We just need to leave him alone.

189
00:11:19,640 --> 00:11:21,160
Cong is very sensible.

190
00:11:24,280 --> 00:11:25,000
I understand.

191
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:27,920
Have some water.

192
00:11:55,480 --> 00:12:00,440
[Dolls → Poisonous Perfume
Let It Go]

193
00:12:01,480 --> 00:12:02,720
I need to ask you for something.

194
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:03,680
Go ahead, mentor.

195
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,480
I'm listening.

196
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:07,640
Even though we took down Group E,

197
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,320
the police are still investigating

198
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,080
Sa Ziyi's death.

199
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:14,320
I've always thought it was suspicious.

200
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:17,040
We still don't know

201
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,120
who left those dolls.

202
00:12:18,400 --> 00:12:20,080
So I want you

203
00:12:20,880 --> 00:12:22,800
to catch

204
00:12:23,520 --> 00:12:26,080
that scheming villain for me.

205
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,040
Mr. Guo.

206
00:12:40,160 --> 00:12:40,840
Mr. Guo.

207
00:12:41,240 --> 00:12:41,840
Liu,

208
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:42,640
you wanted to see me?

209
00:12:43,840 --> 00:12:44,840
Here's the thing, Mr. Guo.

210
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:46,840
We all heard

211
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,040
what happened to Chen.

212
00:12:48,880 --> 00:12:49,880
He was such a good man.

213
00:12:50,680 --> 00:12:52,320
He was always so kind

214
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,160
to us cleaning staff.

215
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:56,120
But Mr. Guo,

216
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:58,320
you need to take care of yourself.

217
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:01,880
I will.

218
00:13:32,400 --> 00:13:33,960
As long as we stand guard,

219
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:36,040
no enemy will ever make it past us.

220
00:13:36,400 --> 00:13:37,200
Cong,

221
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:38,440
remember.

222
00:13:40,080 --> 00:13:42,000
This is what we're here to defend.

223
00:14:21,520 --> 00:14:22,680
Mr. Guo, I brought you breakfast.

224
00:14:22,680 --> 00:14:23,680
Have a few bites.

225
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:25,800
I'm fine.

226
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:27,600
Skipping a meal won't kill me.

227
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:33,920
Mr. Guo.

228
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,160
Let me take over.

229
00:14:35,160 --> 00:14:36,080
You go get some rest.

230
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:38,560
- Okay. - Go.

231
00:14:47,120 --> 00:14:47,920
Yu.

232
00:14:48,560 --> 00:14:49,920
If Mr. Guo keeps this up,

233
00:14:49,920 --> 00:14:51,000
he's going to collapse.

234
00:14:51,080 --> 00:14:51,760
You should talk to him.

235
00:14:53,160 --> 00:14:54,280
It wouldn't help if I did.

236
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:55,560
So do you think

237
00:14:55,560 --> 00:14:58,400
this is some kind of
post-traumatic stress reaction?

238
00:15:00,360 --> 00:15:02,760
Maybe it's not that simple.

239
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:05,800
Have you noticed

240
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:08,360
he hasn't mentioned
Group E at all lately?

241
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,040
Sometimes
when Shihuo and Dayu bring it up,

242
00:15:11,040 --> 00:15:12,720
he just walks away

243
00:15:12,760 --> 00:15:13,680
without a word.

244
00:15:13,760 --> 00:15:15,280
He's avoiding it on purpose.

245
00:15:15,400 --> 00:15:18,000
From a psychological standpoint,

246
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:20,080
that's often a sign of lost confidence.

247
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,080
Mr. Guo, lacking confidence?

248
00:15:23,000 --> 00:15:24,000
I'm just guessing.

249
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:25,560
Let's keep an eye on it.

250
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,160
Mr. Guo.

251
00:15:35,520 --> 00:15:37,080
Mr. Guo, I need to use the bathroom.

252
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:37,920
Can you take over?

253
00:15:38,160 --> 00:15:38,960
Sure. Go ahead.

254
00:15:50,680 --> 00:15:51,320
Bowen.

255
00:15:51,680 --> 00:15:52,280
Bowen.

256
00:15:57,920 --> 00:15:59,040
Hello, China Customs.

257
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:03,760
Please open it yourself.

258
00:16:08,880 --> 00:16:09,360
Okay.

259
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:14,680
Mr. Guo.

260
00:16:15,640 --> 00:16:16,800
I warmed up some soy milk
and fried dough sticks for you.

261
00:16:16,800 --> 00:16:17,800
At least have a bite.

262
00:16:18,520 --> 00:16:20,000
Thanks. I'm not hungry yet.

263
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,680
I'll watch things here.

264
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:24,120
You go rest for a bit.

265
00:16:25,040 --> 00:16:26,600
I don't think Wei can talk him into it.

266
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,000
Shihuo, go try.

267
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,120
Make him go home and sleep.

268
00:16:29,400 --> 00:16:31,000
He's going to collapse at this rate.

269
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:32,160
Me?

270
00:16:32,880 --> 00:16:34,280
You think I can talk him into it?

271
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:34,920
No.

272
00:16:35,240 --> 00:16:36,440
I'll go find Mr. Shen.

273
00:16:37,120 --> 00:16:37,960
We can't convince Mr. Guo.

274
00:16:38,040 --> 00:16:39,280
But he'll listen to Mr. Shen.

275
00:16:59,360 --> 00:16:59,880
Cong,

276
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:01,000
shift's over.

277
00:17:01,280 --> 00:17:01,800
Go home.

278
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:04,640
Your mother called me yesterday.

279
00:17:04,760 --> 00:17:07,120
She made me promise
to get you home safe.

280
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:08,680
You head back.

281
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:09,680
I don't want to go home yet.

282
00:17:12,440 --> 00:17:13,960
That won't do.

283
00:17:14,080 --> 00:17:14,800
Right?

284
00:17:15,040 --> 00:17:15,800
You've been here

285
00:17:15,800 --> 00:17:16,800
all day, every day.

286
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:17,840
Staying up here every night.

287
00:17:17,840 --> 00:17:18,840
You can't go on like this.

288
00:17:19,560 --> 00:17:20,520
Let me tell you something.

289
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:21,720
Your eye sockets

290
00:17:21,760 --> 00:17:22,960
are already sunken in.

291
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:24,320
Just go home.

292
00:17:24,320 --> 00:17:25,360
You've had a long day.

293
00:17:27,920 --> 00:17:29,320
If you keep this up,

294
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:31,200
we might have to get creative.

295
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,120
Come on, Bowen.

296
00:17:32,320 --> 00:17:33,480
Escort Mr. Guo off the premises.

297
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,280
- Hey, you… - Don't touch me!

298
00:17:37,560 --> 00:17:38,800
Can't I just have some peace?

299
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:47,920
Mr. Guo.

300
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:49,480
Come to my office.

301
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:05,240
Everyone's worried about you.

302
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:06,720
They want you to go home and rest.

303
00:18:06,760 --> 00:18:08,440
Throwing your weight around, huh?

304
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:09,760
Here.

305
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:11,760
I've got a desk right here.

306
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:13,160
Go ahead, slam on this one.

307
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:14,640
Slam it!

308
00:18:25,760 --> 00:18:26,520
Guo Cong,

309
00:18:27,320 --> 00:18:29,280
look at yourself.

310
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:30,440
How long

311
00:18:30,480 --> 00:18:32,800
can you last without eating or sleeping?

312
00:18:33,320 --> 00:18:35,320
Is this what your mentor would want?

313
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:36,840
You think you can

314
00:18:36,840 --> 00:18:38,240
take down Group E like this?

315
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:41,560
Mr. Shen.

316
00:18:46,000 --> 00:18:47,040
My mentor died

317
00:18:47,040 --> 00:18:47,880
with regrets.

318
00:18:48,440 --> 00:18:48,920
I…

319
00:18:50,240 --> 00:18:52,400
I feel so guilty and so desperate.

320
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:54,480
The only thing I can do now is work.

321
00:18:57,240 --> 00:18:58,720
I understand how you feel.

322
00:18:59,360 --> 00:19:00,760
But I don't agree
with what you're doing.

323
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:02,520
To protect you,

324
00:19:03,080 --> 00:19:04,840
we're putting you on leave.

325
00:19:07,280 --> 00:19:08,640
Take this opportunity

326
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:10,360
to sort things out.

327
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:14,680
Yes, sir.

328
00:19:18,280 --> 00:19:19,200
Guo Cong.

329
00:19:21,200 --> 00:19:22,560
Don't put too much pressure on yourself.

330
00:19:22,840 --> 00:19:23,640
We're all here.

331
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:26,200
Yes, sir.

332
00:19:38,080 --> 00:19:38,800
Chef,

333
00:19:38,800 --> 00:19:40,640
have you started on their order yet?

334
00:19:40,680 --> 00:19:42,280
Is it ready yet? Hurry up.

335
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:45,840
Here.

336
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:48,320
[Yuren Restaurant]

337
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:49,280
[Yuren Restaurant]
Coming right up.

338
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:50,080
[Yuren Restaurant]

339
00:19:50,080 --> 00:19:51,160
[Yuren Restaurant]
- Bring an extra set. - You got it.

340
00:19:53,520 --> 00:19:54,840
They want Coke over there.

341
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:55,720
Yeah.

342
00:19:59,680 --> 00:20:00,680
Excuse me, can we get a menu?

343
00:20:00,680 --> 00:20:01,320
Alright.

344
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,680
They ordered another dish over here.

345
00:20:07,280 --> 00:20:08,280
Take your time looking.

346
00:20:08,280 --> 00:20:09,120
- Go ahead and order. - Okay.

347
00:20:09,360 --> 00:20:10,280
Right. Clams.

348
00:20:24,040 --> 00:20:25,000
I'm on leave.

349
00:20:26,120 --> 00:20:28,880
I need to clear my head a bit.

350
00:20:29,400 --> 00:20:31,280
Thought I'd crash at your place
for a couple of days.

351
00:20:31,280 --> 00:20:32,880
And help you out with the restaurant.
Is that okay?

352
00:20:33,800 --> 00:20:34,320
Sure.

353
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:36,560
I trust you with the place.

354
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,120
See over there?

355
00:20:40,040 --> 00:20:40,880
There's a bed

356
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:42,400
in that room.

357
00:20:43,120 --> 00:20:44,680
If you're okay sleeping there,

358
00:20:45,160 --> 00:20:46,600
you can make do for a few days.

359
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:47,720
I can handle it.

360
00:20:49,080 --> 00:20:50,400
It's quiet here at night,

361
00:20:51,160 --> 00:20:52,520
but it gets noisy in the morning.

362
00:20:52,640 --> 00:20:53,960
If you don't mind…

363
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:57,280
I don't.

364
00:20:58,720 --> 00:20:59,080
Good.

365
00:20:59,760 --> 00:21:00,880
I'll get back to work then.

366
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:01,880
Thanks, Fei.

367
00:21:03,240 --> 00:21:07,080
[Customs Dormitory]

368
00:21:07,080 --> 00:21:10,800
[Binhai News; Author: Xuan Yangyang
Editor: Jing Xuanlang]

369
00:21:14,480 --> 00:21:16,000
Zheng Ting just posted.

370
00:21:16,320 --> 00:21:18,040
He even uploaded the lawyer's letter.

371
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:19,880
How can he be this shameless?

372
00:21:20,440 --> 00:21:23,160
No. I have to fight back for Mr. Guo.

373
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,080
Don't do anything rash.

374
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:27,520
Getting into a war of words
with them right now is useless.

375
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,480
Netizens aren't going to believe us.

376
00:21:34,160 --> 00:21:36,400
Does fairness even
mean anything anymore?

377
00:21:36,480 --> 00:21:37,840
They're the ones smearing us,

378
00:21:37,840 --> 00:21:39,760
and when we try to clear our name,
no one believes it.

379
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:42,800
So now we need

380
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,200
to think this through.

381
00:21:44,320 --> 00:21:46,040
How do we get Zheng Ting

382
00:21:46,080 --> 00:21:47,720
to prove our innocence himself?

383
00:21:48,680 --> 00:21:49,840
Then let's just go talk to him?

384
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:51,240
That's even worse.

385
00:21:51,760 --> 00:21:53,840
You know the kind of tricks they pull.

386
00:21:54,040 --> 00:21:56,480
If we meet him privately,

387
00:21:56,560 --> 00:21:58,040
and he makes another video,

388
00:21:58,040 --> 00:21:59,440
we'll be in an even worse spot.

389
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:02,000
Can't go after him openly
or behind the scenes.

390
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:03,440
So what are we supposed to do?

391
00:22:05,640 --> 00:22:06,560
Look.

392
00:22:06,560 --> 00:22:07,720
I was just searching online

393
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:09,720
for news about Zheng Ting.

394
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:10,440
[The Rising Star
of the Luxury Goods Trade]

395
00:22:10,440 --> 00:22:11,320
[The Rising Star]
I found out

396
00:22:11,440 --> 00:22:13,960
[of the Luxury Goods Trade]
he's actually a high-end buyer.

397
00:22:14,440 --> 00:22:16,600
He sells off watches
that have appreciation potential

398
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:18,680
at their peak.

399
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,640
He doesn't collect them at all.

400
00:22:21,240 --> 00:22:24,080
So I think

401
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:27,080
we should focus on the buyers.

402
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:29,240
That means

403
00:22:29,800 --> 00:22:32,200
we need to find the potential buyers

404
00:22:32,200 --> 00:22:33,600
for these watches.

405
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:38,600
Too bad

406
00:22:39,520 --> 00:22:41,320
I don't know anything
about rich people's circles.

407
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:46,400
I'll just go home tomorrow.

408
00:22:47,160 --> 00:22:47,880
Wouldn't that do it?

409
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,400
Right!

410
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:56,240
We're counting on you, girl.

411
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:57,360
Consider it done.

412
00:22:58,240 --> 00:22:59,680
Great.

413
00:23:00,840 --> 00:23:01,720
Heroine!

414
00:23:04,720 --> 00:23:07,680
[Power Off]

415
00:23:33,320 --> 00:23:34,840
[Mentor, are you doing okay?]

416
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:42,400
Mentor, are you doing okay?

417
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:50,200
Dayu and the others said you're fine

418
00:23:50,480 --> 00:23:52,240
and that I'm worrying for nothing.

419
00:23:54,400 --> 00:23:57,040
So just get some rest.

420
00:23:58,280 --> 00:23:58,960
Good night.

421
00:24:55,520 --> 00:24:56,120
She's home?

422
00:24:57,160 --> 00:24:57,880
Yes.

423
00:24:57,880 --> 00:24:58,720
She's upstairs.

424
00:25:00,800 --> 00:25:01,840
I'll be in the living room.

425
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:07,520
Putting on an act.

426
00:25:16,800 --> 00:25:17,400
Thanks.

427
00:25:18,080 --> 00:25:19,320
Hey, Ms. Tang.

428
00:25:19,720 --> 00:25:21,760
Make a few
of Xiaoyan's favorite dishes today.

429
00:25:22,160 --> 00:25:23,120
I want a drink.

430
00:25:23,440 --> 00:25:24,120
Got it.

431
00:25:36,400 --> 00:25:38,200
Dad, you're home.

432
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:40,960
Our princess is back.

433
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:45,480
Who's been missing her
every single day at home?

434
00:25:45,560 --> 00:25:47,280
Don't be sarcastic.

435
00:25:48,520 --> 00:25:49,640
That would be me.

436
00:25:49,840 --> 00:25:52,000
Who wouldn't worry
about their little girl?

437
00:25:53,000 --> 00:25:54,400
Dad, I'm sorry.

438
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:56,440
I won't fight with you anymore.

439
00:25:57,280 --> 00:25:58,040
Hold on.

440
00:25:58,320 --> 00:26:00,440
You apologized way too fast this time.

441
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:01,960
You need something from me, don't you?

442
00:26:03,520 --> 00:26:05,120
You know me best, Dad.

443
00:26:10,440 --> 00:26:11,040
Dad.

444
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:13,080
Cut the smirk.

445
00:26:13,880 --> 00:26:16,000
That's not over yet,
as far as I'm concerned.

446
00:26:16,520 --> 00:26:18,640
Dad, no need to turn the page.
It's still the same story.

447
00:26:19,160 --> 00:26:20,000
Do you remember

448
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:22,200
that video that falsely accused us?

449
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:23,560
How could he not?

450
00:26:23,880 --> 00:26:25,800
Your dad practically watches that video

451
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:27,080
every single day.

452
00:26:28,560 --> 00:26:29,680
And he said

453
00:26:30,400 --> 00:26:32,200
that people who don't know the truth

454
00:26:32,240 --> 00:26:34,400
just see you showing off,

455
00:26:35,160 --> 00:26:37,760
but he sees a sense of justice in you.

456
00:26:38,240 --> 00:26:40,560
He even said

457
00:26:40,880 --> 00:26:43,120
you remind him of himself
when he was young.

458
00:26:43,200 --> 00:26:45,600
Of course. I know my own daughter.

459
00:26:46,360 --> 00:26:48,200
Even a fortune wouldn't impress you,

460
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,120
let alone make you flaunt it.

461
00:26:50,040 --> 00:26:50,800
Xiaoyan,

462
00:26:51,480 --> 00:26:53,070
I wasn't really

463
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,840
against you working at Customs.

464
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:58,320
I was afraid you couldn't handle
the hard work.

465
00:26:58,600 --> 00:27:00,040
What is Customs?

466
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,480
It's the nation's gateway.

467
00:27:02,000 --> 00:27:03,040
Not a game.

468
00:27:03,720 --> 00:27:05,800
Not a place for a spoiled rich girl.

469
00:27:07,080 --> 00:27:07,720
But

470
00:27:08,160 --> 00:27:09,240
over this past year,

471
00:27:09,600 --> 00:27:11,360
I've seen you change.

472
00:27:12,680 --> 00:27:14,000
What makes me happy is

473
00:27:14,400 --> 00:27:15,880
that you've finally found

474
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:18,560
something you love and want to protect.

475
00:27:18,680 --> 00:27:19,960
My little girl has grown up.

476
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:24,560
Thank you, Dad.

477
00:27:26,200 --> 00:27:26,800
Alright.

478
00:27:27,440 --> 00:27:28,560
Enough with the sentiment.

479
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:32,120
Now tell me

480
00:27:32,320 --> 00:27:33,640
what you need me to do.

481
00:27:40,200 --> 00:27:41,040
Give me a straight answer.

482
00:27:41,040 --> 00:27:41,960
Are you in or not?

483
00:27:42,600 --> 00:27:43,360
Shouldn't we

484
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:47,360
talk it over with Shihuo and the others?

485
00:27:47,360 --> 00:27:49,720
No. If we do, it won't happen.

486
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:51,800
Everyone at Customs is on edge
about Mr. Guo right now.

487
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:54,160
If they find out,
they'll study it for days.

488
00:27:54,160 --> 00:27:55,560
And we'll miss our chance.

489
00:27:57,600 --> 00:27:58,200
Yu.

490
00:27:58,320 --> 00:27:59,280
Don't look at Yu.

491
00:27:59,920 --> 00:28:01,080
This was her idea.

492
00:28:04,280 --> 00:28:06,520
Last night, Xiaoyan and I went over it.

493
00:28:06,800 --> 00:28:08,040
Shouldn't be too risky.

494
00:28:08,040 --> 00:28:09,520
Even if it doesn't work out,

495
00:28:09,520 --> 00:28:10,680
it won't come back on Customs.

496
00:28:10,920 --> 00:28:11,640
Exactly.

497
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:14,720
Yan Bowen,

498
00:28:15,400 --> 00:28:17,360
you had no problem
defending me online.

499
00:28:17,400 --> 00:28:18,320
Why are you being such a coward

500
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:19,440
when it comes to Mr. Guo?

501
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,640
I'm not a coward.

502
00:28:21,280 --> 00:28:22,600
That was online.

503
00:28:22,600 --> 00:28:25,280
Now we have to… act.

504
00:28:25,360 --> 00:28:26,840
I'm not an actor.

505
00:28:26,880 --> 00:28:27,360
Fine.

506
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:28,680
Then it's settled.

507
00:28:28,680 --> 00:28:32,720
[Classic Men's Haircuts
'Chestnut' Style]

508
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:36,080
Look at me.

509
00:28:36,080 --> 00:28:38,200
[Classic Men's Haircuts]

510
00:28:39,600 --> 00:28:41,200
[Classic Men's Haircuts
'Chestnut' Style]

511
00:28:44,360 --> 00:28:45,920
Yu, you have to help me.

512
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:48,480
It's impossible to find a good haircut
for his face shape.

513
00:28:48,600 --> 00:28:49,320
None of them looks good.

514
00:28:49,760 --> 00:28:50,400
Turn around.

515
00:28:57,760 --> 00:28:58,920
Never mind. I can't tell.

516
00:28:58,920 --> 00:28:59,880
You decide.

517
00:29:01,280 --> 00:29:02,560
Me?

518
00:29:05,400 --> 00:29:06,520
How about

519
00:29:07,240 --> 00:29:07,840
this one?

520
00:29:08,160 --> 00:29:10,280
This one looks fresh and bright,

521
00:29:10,320 --> 00:29:11,520
kinda refined,

522
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:12,680
like he's got some class.

523
00:29:14,200 --> 00:29:14,880
I like it.

524
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:15,440
Okay?

525
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:16,080
Yes.

526
00:29:22,040 --> 00:29:22,600
Don't move.

527
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:26,080
Are you sure you don't want to
ask for my opinion?

528
00:29:28,960 --> 00:29:29,840
Get to work,

529
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:31,000
Stylist Lyu.

530
00:29:31,080 --> 00:29:31,760
Okay.

531
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:34,920
Here.

532
00:29:34,960 --> 00:29:35,920
Close your eyes.

533
00:29:39,960 --> 00:29:40,920
You're holding it backwards.

534
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:48,080
Shh.

535
00:29:52,960 --> 00:29:53,640
Don't move.

536
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:56,600
I'm not moving a muscle.

537
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:05,080
Let's see how it looks.

538
00:30:06,160 --> 00:30:06,640
Nice.

539
00:30:06,640 --> 00:30:07,280
Okay.

540
00:30:09,640 --> 00:30:10,120
Can I…

541
00:30:10,240 --> 00:30:13,000
take this eye mask off?

542
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:13,920
It's burning up.

543
00:30:14,400 --> 00:30:15,440
What are you talking about?

544
00:30:15,440 --> 00:30:16,720
I sleep in this every single night.

545
00:30:16,720 --> 00:30:17,760
You're so delicate.

546
00:30:19,800 --> 00:30:20,440
There.

547
00:30:20,520 --> 00:30:21,080
Next step.

548
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:25,120
Tie, suit, belt, and shoes.

549
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,520
Try them on and show me.

550
00:30:26,720 --> 00:30:27,120
Got it?

551
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:30,240
All mine?

552
00:30:30,240 --> 00:30:32,120
In your dreams. I borrowed them.

553
00:30:32,600 --> 00:30:33,280
Go change.

554
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:36,800
Got it.

555
00:30:38,360 --> 00:30:38,920
Got it.

556
00:30:42,920 --> 00:30:43,600
Hurry up.

557
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:56,120
Yu.

558
00:30:56,800 --> 00:30:57,760
When do you think

559
00:30:58,440 --> 00:31:01,240
we'll get to be mentors for a day?

560
00:31:01,720 --> 00:31:02,480
What,

561
00:31:02,840 --> 00:31:04,080
you just figured out
how to be a trainee,

562
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:05,040
and now you want to be a mentor?

563
00:31:05,520 --> 00:31:06,120
No.

564
00:31:06,800 --> 00:31:08,160
I just think

565
00:31:08,440 --> 00:31:10,160
our mentors have it really hard.

566
00:31:10,600 --> 00:31:11,840
I want to see what it's like.

567
00:31:12,640 --> 00:31:13,320
Look,

568
00:31:13,760 --> 00:31:15,160
my mentor, Deng,

569
00:31:15,280 --> 00:31:18,080
devoted her entire youth to her job.

570
00:31:18,440 --> 00:31:20,280
In her middle years,
she gave up her dreams

571
00:31:20,280 --> 00:31:21,520
and dedicated herself to her family.

572
00:31:21,920 --> 00:31:23,280
Mr. Guo's mentor

573
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:26,040
gave his whole life
to Passenger Inspection.

574
00:31:27,960 --> 00:31:28,760
Now

575
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:30,720
it's our turn to protect your mentor.

576
00:31:35,960 --> 00:31:36,760
Thank you.

577
00:31:54,640 --> 00:31:55,400
Yu!

578
00:31:56,240 --> 00:31:56,840
Come here!

579
00:31:56,920 --> 00:31:57,440
Okay.

580
00:32:01,200 --> 00:32:01,640
Fei.

581
00:32:02,320 --> 00:32:02,840
Yu.

582
00:32:04,000 --> 00:32:05,400
Did you clean this up?

583
00:32:05,640 --> 00:32:06,280
No.

584
00:32:06,280 --> 00:32:07,240
Cong did.

585
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:09,640
Okay.

586
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:11,160
Go back to work.

587
00:32:11,200 --> 00:32:12,000
Got it, Fei.

588
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:08,600
It's the right place.

589
00:33:22,320 --> 00:33:23,080
I didn't see you.

590
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:24,840
You didn't see me?

591
00:33:25,240 --> 00:33:26,920
I was standing right here

592
00:33:26,920 --> 00:33:27,320
waving at you.

593
00:33:27,320 --> 00:33:28,440
You zoomed right past me.

594
00:33:28,440 --> 00:33:29,560
And you're telling me you didn't see me?

595
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:31,400
I really didn't.

596
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:36,800
You don't usually dress like this.

597
00:33:39,440 --> 00:33:40,080
What?

598
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:41,840
Doesn't it look good?

599
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:43,040
It looks good.

600
00:33:43,480 --> 00:33:44,320
Really good.

601
00:33:44,320 --> 00:33:44,840
Seriously.

602
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:46,360
That's more like it.

603
00:33:49,880 --> 00:33:50,480
My dad's.

604
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:53,000
Is that real?

605
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:54,240
Of course.

606
00:33:54,240 --> 00:33:55,680
This watch is over 600,000 yuan.

607
00:33:56,480 --> 00:33:57,560
I… I'm not wearing this.

608
00:33:57,800 --> 00:33:59,120
Just wear it.

609
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:01,280
We're playing a rich couple today.

610
00:34:01,280 --> 00:34:02,840
This kind of prop is essential.

611
00:34:03,160 --> 00:34:04,960
And that outfit you're wearing
is also a prop.

612
00:34:04,960 --> 00:34:06,080
Don't you get it dirty.

613
00:34:06,120 --> 00:34:07,360
I have to give it back later.

614
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:08,800
Why don't we

615
00:34:09,320 --> 00:34:11,080
just play brother and sister today?

616
00:34:11,360 --> 00:34:12,480
Do we even look alike?

617
00:34:12,920 --> 00:34:13,560
Besides,

618
00:34:13,640 --> 00:34:15,520
there might be people at the expo
who know me.

619
00:34:16,000 --> 00:34:17,080
I'm an only child.

620
00:34:17,080 --> 00:34:18,560
If they find out, we're screwed.

621
00:34:19,160 --> 00:34:20,280
Let's go, honey.

622
00:34:20,960 --> 00:34:22,320
Hold on. Let me turn the car around.

623
00:34:23,240 --> 00:34:24,160
Don't bother.

624
00:34:24,160 --> 00:34:25,120
Dressed like this,

625
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:26,600
we can't drive that car.

626
00:34:27,240 --> 00:34:28,040
Today,

627
00:34:28,040 --> 00:34:29,120
I'm treating you to something fancy.

628
00:34:29,480 --> 00:34:30,280
We're driving my dad's car.

629
00:34:38,080 --> 00:34:39,440
If I scratch it,

630
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:40,920
I… I can't afford to fix it.

631
00:34:41,080 --> 00:34:41,800
I can't drive it.

632
00:34:42,640 --> 00:34:44,440
If I say you can, you can.

633
00:34:44,720 --> 00:34:45,400
Get in.

634
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,240
Let me lock my car first.

635
00:35:22,720 --> 00:35:24,280
Don't be nervous. Act normal.

636
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:27,400
Act normal.

637
00:35:27,840 --> 00:35:28,240
Okay.

638
00:35:28,800 --> 00:35:30,400
Just don't let anyone see through us.

639
00:35:47,600 --> 00:35:48,680
That man.

640
00:35:49,040 --> 00:35:50,280
That man is He Wei.

641
00:35:50,600 --> 00:35:52,760
Zheng Ting's biggest watch buyer.

642
00:35:53,200 --> 00:35:54,240
From what I know,

643
00:35:54,240 --> 00:35:56,240
Zheng Ting has already talked
to him privately.

644
00:35:56,240 --> 00:35:57,400
Just watch me.

645
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,160
Play it by ear.

646
00:35:58,160 --> 00:35:59,240
Be sharp. Got it?

647
00:35:59,560 --> 00:36:00,160
Sharp.

648
00:36:00,560 --> 00:36:01,040
Got it.

649
00:36:06,920 --> 00:36:07,720
Mr. He?

650
00:36:09,440 --> 00:36:10,240
Mr. He,

651
00:36:10,520 --> 00:36:11,120
hello.

652
00:36:11,960 --> 00:36:12,440
Hello.

653
00:36:12,800 --> 00:36:13,920
I'm a watch enthusiast.

654
00:36:13,920 --> 00:36:15,040
I've always admired you.

655
00:36:15,160 --> 00:36:16,200
Seeing you today,

656
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:17,960
you're truly elegant.

657
00:36:18,320 --> 00:36:18,920
Thank you.

658
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:26,800
[Ashamed to chase vain glory;
disdaining to befriend empty talkers]

659
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:27,800
Mr. He,

660
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:29,080
you not only know watches,

661
00:36:29,360 --> 00:36:30,280
but calligraphy too?

662
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:31,880
Everyone knows

663
00:36:32,000 --> 00:36:33,200
Mr. Qi Baishi's paintings,

664
00:36:33,360 --> 00:36:35,840
but few know his semi-cursive script
is just as remarkable.

665
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:38,280
His semi-cursive script

666
00:36:38,280 --> 00:36:40,040
still carries
the brushwork of seal script.

667
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:41,880
It feels fresh and natural.

668
00:36:41,880 --> 00:36:44,200
The biggest feature
lies in its use of brush and ink.

669
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,720
The strokes are thick and heavy,

670
00:36:45,960 --> 00:36:47,280
yet not clumsy,

671
00:36:47,640 --> 00:36:49,200
but rather lively and agile.

672
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:52,680
And the strength of his script

673
00:36:52,800 --> 00:36:54,000
lies in its posture.

674
00:36:54,320 --> 00:36:57,080
Every character has a slight tilt.

675
00:36:57,160 --> 00:36:57,960
The angle is small,

676
00:36:58,280 --> 00:36:59,680
but the visual impact is striking.

677
00:36:59,800 --> 00:37:01,120
For example,
in this five-character couplet,

678
00:37:01,120 --> 00:37:02,120
the first character of each line

679
00:37:02,120 --> 00:37:04,560
leans lower on the left
and higher on the right.

680
00:37:04,760 --> 00:37:07,120
It captures an upward, soaring beauty.

681
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:13,840
Hello.

682
00:37:14,160 --> 00:37:16,080
May I have your name?

683
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:17,240
I'm Bowen.

684
00:37:17,440 --> 00:37:18,000
I only know the basics.

685
00:37:19,880 --> 00:37:21,360
Young man, you're being modest.

686
00:37:22,160 --> 00:37:23,680
When I first looked at this piece,

687
00:37:23,680 --> 00:37:24,840
I thought it was good,

688
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,200
but I couldn't pinpoint why.

689
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:28,000
After your analysis,

690
00:37:28,520 --> 00:37:30,520
I find it even more lively.

691
00:37:31,560 --> 00:37:32,920
Mr. He, you flatter me.

692
00:37:33,240 --> 00:37:35,040
As they say,
everyone has their specialty.

693
00:37:35,040 --> 00:37:37,080
Your expertise in the watch world

694
00:37:37,200 --> 00:37:38,680
is well known.

695
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:40,800
My wife and I saw you standing here

696
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:42,600
for a long time.

697
00:37:42,600 --> 00:37:44,680
You must have appreciated

698
00:37:44,840 --> 00:37:46,960
the nobility and elegance

699
00:37:47,160 --> 00:37:47,880
expressed

700
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:48,920
in this calligraphy.

701
00:37:49,280 --> 00:37:52,240
It matches the integrity you seek,

702
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:53,520
doesn't it?

703
00:37:54,360 --> 00:37:55,360
You're too kind.

704
00:37:56,160 --> 00:37:57,960
I wouldn't say nobility and elegance.

705
00:37:58,360 --> 00:37:59,960
But many people say I have

706
00:37:59,960 --> 00:38:00,960
a cleanliness fetish.

707
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:03,200
That's because what I set my eyes on

708
00:38:03,400 --> 00:38:05,160
must have a clear origin.

709
00:38:07,160 --> 00:38:09,160
For a collector,

710
00:38:09,200 --> 00:38:11,440
the provenance of a piece

711
00:38:11,520 --> 00:38:12,280
is certainly important.

712
00:38:12,520 --> 00:38:13,880
That's only natural, Mr. He.

713
00:38:17,960 --> 00:38:18,840
Right.

714
00:38:18,880 --> 00:38:21,240
We took the liberty of interrupting you

715
00:38:21,240 --> 00:38:22,440
because a ten-million-yuan watch

716
00:38:22,440 --> 00:38:24,800
has recently surfaced in Binhai.

717
00:38:25,120 --> 00:38:27,160
My father
is interested in collecting it.

718
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:29,400
But I'm really not sure about it.

719
00:38:29,600 --> 00:38:31,800
When I saw you today,

720
00:38:31,960 --> 00:38:34,080
I figured I should ask for your advice.

721
00:38:34,320 --> 00:38:35,600
And your father is...?

722
00:38:35,880 --> 00:38:37,160
Lyu Wenwu.

723
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,160
Oh, Mr. Lyu.

724
00:38:40,560 --> 00:38:42,680
I've met him a few times.

725
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:44,720
Is he here today?

726
00:38:44,960 --> 00:38:46,880
He's got something to take care of today

727
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:48,960
and asked us to come and learn.

728
00:38:51,360 --> 00:38:51,960
Here's the thing.

729
00:38:53,480 --> 00:38:55,120
The watch you mentioned

730
00:38:55,440 --> 00:38:57,880
should be the one
Zheng Ting brought back

731
00:38:58,080 --> 00:38:59,320
from an overseas auction.

732
00:39:00,160 --> 00:39:00,840
It's clean.

733
00:39:01,960 --> 00:39:03,520
Haven't you heard?

734
00:39:03,680 --> 00:39:06,360
There's a bit of a story
with Zheng Ting's watch.

735
00:39:06,440 --> 00:39:08,400
It's all over the internet right now.

736
00:39:09,960 --> 00:39:10,400
Here.

737
00:39:10,600 --> 00:39:11,280
Take a look.

738
00:39:13,160 --> 00:39:14,840
There are rumors online

739
00:39:14,840 --> 00:39:16,080
that the watch was seized

740
00:39:16,080 --> 00:39:17,320
by Customs

741
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:19,640
and that someone at Customs
even wore it out to show off.

742
00:39:19,640 --> 00:39:22,240
If it got swapped out
during the process,

743
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:23,760
that would be a serious problem.

744
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:25,760
Zheng Ting has already sued Customs.

745
00:39:26,000 --> 00:39:27,240
This has gone too far.

746
00:39:28,480 --> 00:39:29,400
Is that so?

747
00:39:29,920 --> 00:39:30,680
Mr. He,

748
00:39:30,840 --> 00:39:32,480
with these rumors going around,

749
00:39:32,600 --> 00:39:33,680
I guess Mr. Zheng

750
00:39:33,680 --> 00:39:35,080
is pretty upset.

751
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:37,440
He sued Customs to prove

752
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:38,640
the watch's authenticity.

753
00:39:39,320 --> 00:39:40,520
Honestly,

754
00:39:40,920 --> 00:39:42,640
I trust Customs.

755
00:39:42,920 --> 00:39:45,240
But this watch is extremely valuable.

756
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:46,320
It's worth ten million yuan.

757
00:39:46,680 --> 00:39:48,080
I'm just worried

758
00:39:48,480 --> 00:39:50,320
that my father…

759
00:39:52,880 --> 00:39:53,560
Thank you.

760
00:39:56,640 --> 00:39:58,320
I think I understand.

761
00:39:59,280 --> 00:40:00,440
Given what's happened,

762
00:40:00,440 --> 00:40:02,040
your father should

763
00:40:02,440 --> 00:40:03,440
be cautious.

764
00:40:04,840 --> 00:40:05,720
I'm sorry.

765
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:06,680
I have to go.

766
00:40:06,760 --> 00:40:07,520
Excuse me.

767
00:40:07,720 --> 00:40:08,520
You go ahead.

768
00:40:19,080 --> 00:40:19,960
I think

769
00:40:20,240 --> 00:40:21,000
we got somewhere.

770
00:40:22,200 --> 00:40:23,320
I think so, too.

771
00:40:24,560 --> 00:40:25,960
Should we get out of here?

772
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:27,600
Aren't you hungry?

773
00:40:27,880 --> 00:40:28,440
No.

774
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:30,240
Maybe you are.

775
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:31,560
Okay.

776
00:40:31,920 --> 00:40:33,000
I am… a little hungry.

777
00:40:34,040 --> 00:40:34,480
Let's go.

778
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:36,440
Go eat something with your 'wife'.

779
00:40:47,480 --> 00:40:48,960
Nobody knows you here.

780
00:40:49,440 --> 00:40:50,680
I… I'm afraid

781
00:40:50,680 --> 00:40:52,160
I'll get this suit dirty.

782
00:40:52,160 --> 00:40:52,640
If I can't

783
00:40:52,640 --> 00:40:53,800
return it, I'm screwed.

784
00:40:55,360 --> 00:40:56,080
Oh, stop.

785
00:40:57,320 --> 00:40:58,600
I'm starving.

786
00:40:59,000 --> 00:40:59,840
Come on.

787
00:41:00,000 --> 00:41:00,720
Ma'am,

788
00:41:00,840 --> 00:41:02,160
two rice noodle rolls, please.

789
00:41:02,160 --> 00:41:03,280
Okay. Coming right up.

790
00:41:17,800 --> 00:41:18,840
What are you doing?

791
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:21,240
Cleaning…

792
00:41:22,160 --> 00:41:22,720
Seriously, Yan Bowen,

793
00:41:22,720 --> 00:41:24,200
you're not particular
when you should be,

794
00:41:24,200 --> 00:41:26,120
but you are when you shouldn't.

795
00:41:26,360 --> 00:41:27,240
Just sit down.

796
00:41:28,920 --> 00:41:30,640
Are you worried about your image?

797
00:41:30,640 --> 00:41:32,000
Nobody knows you here.

798
00:41:35,000 --> 00:41:36,120
Well…

799
00:41:36,120 --> 00:41:37,000
I'll sit then.

800
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:38,600
Don't blame me

801
00:41:38,640 --> 00:41:39,480
if the suit gets dirty.

802
00:41:40,040 --> 00:41:40,960
I won't.

803
00:41:41,080 --> 00:41:41,720
Just eat.

804
00:41:41,720 --> 00:41:43,480
Skewers like these
are no good once they go cold.

805
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:44,400
Okay.

806
00:41:45,800 --> 00:41:48,120
You're acting really weird today.

807
00:41:49,000 --> 00:41:49,480
Am I?

808
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:50,400
Yeah.

809
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:54,960
I didn't know

810
00:41:55,080 --> 00:41:56,440
you had it in you.

811
00:41:57,720 --> 00:41:59,920
You sound like an expert
when you talk about that calligraphy.

812
00:42:01,640 --> 00:42:02,800
Just a coincidence.

813
00:42:03,240 --> 00:42:04,160
I've been reading

814
00:42:04,160 --> 00:42:05,800
about Qi Baishi lately.

815
00:42:06,160 --> 00:42:07,720
Never thought I'd use it.

816
00:42:08,040 --> 00:42:09,320
How did you know

817
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:11,080
that approach would work on He Wei?

818
00:42:12,720 --> 00:42:13,760
I just figured

819
00:42:13,960 --> 00:42:15,320
he's a watch collector.

820
00:42:15,440 --> 00:42:17,040
If I tried to talk about watches,

821
00:42:17,080 --> 00:42:18,360
I'd give myself away.

822
00:42:18,560 --> 00:42:20,240
So building trust through something

823
00:42:20,240 --> 00:42:21,400
he's not familiar with

824
00:42:21,400 --> 00:42:22,200
should be easier.

825
00:42:22,560 --> 00:42:23,880
I took some time today

826
00:42:23,960 --> 00:42:25,120
to look up interviews

827
00:42:25,120 --> 00:42:26,520
with He Wei.

828
00:42:26,600 --> 00:42:28,000
I found out

829
00:42:28,520 --> 00:42:30,440
he really cares about the origin

830
00:42:30,640 --> 00:42:31,440
of his collection.

831
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:33,040
He probably

832
00:42:33,040 --> 00:42:35,280
can't stand it if someone else
has tampered with his pieces.

833
00:42:35,560 --> 00:42:37,280
So I deliberately steered
the conversation

834
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:38,960
toward provenance.

835
00:42:39,760 --> 00:42:40,560
Of course,

836
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:41,840
you were great, too.

837
00:42:43,200 --> 00:42:45,160
One look from me,
and you knew what to say.

838
00:42:45,200 --> 00:42:46,360
You totally rattled him.

839
00:42:46,560 --> 00:42:47,680
Absolutely.

840
00:42:48,200 --> 00:42:49,360
Anyway, we pulled off

841
00:42:49,360 --> 00:42:50,520
something big today.

842
00:42:51,040 --> 00:42:53,440
We planted a hidden bomb with He Wei.

843
00:42:53,440 --> 00:42:55,080
Now we just wait for it to go off
with Zheng Ting.

844
00:42:55,080 --> 00:42:55,680
Go off.

845
00:42:56,760 --> 00:42:57,120
Cheers.

846
00:42:57,120 --> 00:42:57,880
Best partners.

847
00:42:57,880 --> 00:42:58,320
Partners.

848
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:37,360
♪There's a place of simple,
everyday warmth♪

849
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:45,000
♪A door left open
for the wandering soul♪

850
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:52,440
♪A humble table still warm with love♪

851
00:43:52,680 --> 00:43:56,320
♪After you've tasted every high and low♪

852
00:43:56,600 --> 00:44:00,240
♪Come home, I'll keep you warm♪

853
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:07,680
♪Where the days begin and end♪

854
00:44:08,400 --> 00:44:15,320
♪A light still on for the ones
who've lost their way♪

855
00:44:16,120 --> 00:44:22,680
♪An embrace waiting just for you♪

856
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:26,680
♪Through every passing season♪

857
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:30,480
♪Even if you return with nothing at all♪

858
00:44:31,120 --> 00:44:34,600
♪Turn around and look♪

859
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:38,600
♪That door's still open♪

860
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:42,440
♪A light still burning♪

861
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:46,240
♪Waiting there for you♪

862
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:49,920
♪Turn around and look♪

863
00:44:50,160 --> 00:44:53,960
